'''Radhakant Nayak''' ({{lang-or|<U+0B30><U+0B3E><U+0B27><U+0B3E><U+0B15><U+0B3E><U+0B02><U+0B24> <U+0B28><U+0B3E><U+0B2F><U+0B15>}}) is an [[India]]n politician belonging to the [[Indian National Congress]] party. He is a Member of the [[Parliament of India]] representing [[Orissa]] in the [[Rajya Sabha]], the upper house of the [[Indian Parliament]]. Radhakant Nayak, a 1962 batch [[Indian Administrative Service|IAS]] officer. Nayak is also connected with the [[Young Men's Christian Association]] (YMCA).

Nayak who served the Central government as Secretary was short-listed for the post of Union Cabinet Secretary during [[H. D. Deve Gowda]] government. However some adverse [[Intelligence Bureau (India)|IB]] report against him came as a hurdle. In 2004 he was elected to Rajya Sabha on Congress ticket.<ref name="it">[http://indiatoday.digitaltoday.in/index.php?option=com_content&task=view&id=17911&sectionid=4&issueid=75&Itemid=1 Cong MP suspected behind VHP leader's murder] India Today - October 18, 2008</ref>

== Controversies ==
In October 2007, the [[Kandhamal district]] Kui Samaj Coordination Committee demanded his resignation. The rationale for the demand was Nayak's support for classifying Panas as [[Kui language (Dravidian)|Kui]] [[adivasi|tribals]], a move that the KSCC opposed.<ref>[http://www.hindu.com/2007/10/15/stories/2007101567230300.htm Kui tribals up in arms in Kandhamal district] The Hindu - October 15, 2007</ref> 

In October 2008, Nayak was accused by local Hindu groups, including the chapters of the [[Bharatiya Janata Party|BJP]] and [[Vishwa Hindu Parishad|VHP]], of being behind the murder of [[Swami Lakshmanananda|Swami Laksmanananda Saraswati]], and police have been investigating persons close to him.<ref name="it" /> Nayak is under investigation by the Orissa Police as of December 2008.<ref>[http://www.indianexpress.com/news/cong-slams-orissa-for-dragging-in-nayaks-name/403752/2 Cong slams Orissa for dragging in Nayak<U+2019>s name] Indian Express - December 28, 2008</ref> Nayak has termed the allegations "defamation and maligning of my character".<ref>[http://www.dailypioneer.com/134836/MP-Nayak-threatens-to-sue-%E2%80%98detractors%E2%80%99.html MP Nayak threatens to sue <U+2018>detractors<U+2019>] The Pioneer - November 17, 2008</ref>

He was amongst around 600 Government servants accused to have produced SC certificates for jobs belonging to Kandhamal against whom investigations are on<ref>http://ibnlive.in.com/news/govt-probes-fake-sc-docs-used-by-ias-ips-officers/81744-3.html##</ref>.

